label.value: spongiotrophoblast cell proliferation

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of spongiotrophoblast cells, resulting in the expansion of the population in the spongiotrophoblast layer.

label.value: regulation of spongiotrophoblast cell proliferation

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of spongiotrophoblast cell proliferation.

label.value: cell proliferation involved in embryonic placenta development

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of the population in the embryonic placenta.

label.value: regulation of cell proliferation involved in embryonic placenta development

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of cell proliferation involved in embryonic placenta development.

label.value: regulation of coreceptor activity

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate or frequency of coreceptor activity, combining with an extracellular or intracellular messenger, and in cooperation with a nearby primary receptor, initiating a change in cell activity.

label.value: intestinal epithelial structure maintenance

value.value: A tissue homeostatic process required for the maintenance of the structure of the intestinal epithelium.

label.value: regulation of intestinal epithelial structure maintenance

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of intestinal epithelial structure maintenance, a tissue homeostatic process required for the maintenance of the structure of the intestinal epithelium.

label.value: positive regulation of intestinal epithelial structure maintenance

value.value: Any process the increases the rate, frequency or extent of intestinal epithelial structure maintenance, a tissue homeostatic process required for the maintenance of the structure of the intestinal epithelium.

label.value: positive regulation of inositol phosphate biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of inositol phosphate biosynthesis. Inositol phosphate biosynthetic processes are the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of an inositol phosphate, 1,2,3,4,5,6-cyclohexanehexol, with one or more phosphate groups attached.

label.value: regulation of endoplasmic reticulum stress-induced eIF2 alpha phosphorylation

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of eIF2 alpha phosphorylation as a cellular response to endoplasmic reticulum stress.

label.value: regulation of eIF2 alpha phosphorylation by dsRNA

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of eIF2 alpha phosphorylation as a cellular response to double-stranded RNA.

label.value: prostate gland growth

value.value: The increase in size or mass of the prostate gland where the increase in size or mass has the specific outcome of the progression of the gland, from its formation to its mature state.

label.value: prostate gland morphogenetic growth

value.value: The differential increase in size or mass of the prostate gland that contributes to the gland attaining its form.

label.value: epithelial-mesenchymal signaling involved in prostate gland development

value.value: Any process that results in the transfer of information from an epithelial cell to a mesenchymal cell where it is interpreted and contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: mesenchymal-epithelial cell signaling involved in prostate gland development

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from a mesenchymal cell to an epithelial cell where it is received and interpreted contributing to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: prostate gland epithelium morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the anatomical structures of epithelia of the prostate gland are generated and organized. An epithelium consists of closely packed cells arranged in one or more layers, that covers the outer surfaces of the body or lines any internal cavity or tube.

label.value: prostate gland stromal morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the prostate gland stroma is generated and organized. The prostate gland stroma is made up of the mesenchymal or fibroblast cells of the prostate gland.

label.value: epithelial cell differentiation involved in prostate gland development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of an epithelial cell of the prostate gland.

label.value: epithelial cell maturation involved in prostate gland development

value.value: The developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for an epithelial cell of the prostate gland to attain its fully functional state. An epithelial cell is a cell usually found in a two-dimensional sheet with a free surface.

label.value: mammary gland branching involved in thelarche

value.value: The process in which the branching structure of the mammary gland duct is generated and organized during the period of sexual maturity in mammals. The mammary gland is a large compound sebaceous gland that in female mammals is modified to secrete milk.

label.value: mammary gland branching involved in pregnancy

value.value: The process in which the branching structure of the mammary gland duct is generated and organized as a part of pregnancy.

label.value: parental behavior

value.value: A reproductive behavior in which a parent cares for and rears offspring.

label.value: oral incubation

value.value: A parental behavior in which fertilized eggs are taken into the mouth and held until hatching.

label.value: tertiary branching involved in mammary gland duct morphogenesis

value.value: The branching process in which the mammary gland ducts form tertiary branches off of the secondary branches as part of diestrus and pregnancy.

label.value: mammary gland alveolus development

value.value: The progression of the mammary gland alveolus over time, from its formation to its mature state. The mammary gland alveolus is a sac-like structure that is found in the mature gland.

label.value: epithelial cell proliferation involved in mammary gland duct elongation

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of mammary gland branch epithelial cells, resulting in the elongation of the branch. The mammary gland branch differs from the bud in that it is not the initial curved portion of the outgrowth.

label.value: branch elongation involved in mammary gland duct branching

value.value: The developmental growth process in which a branch of a mammary gland duct elongates.

label.value: intestinal phytosterol absorption

value.value: A process in which phytosterols are taken up from the contents of the intestine.

label.value: regulation of mast cell chemotaxis

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of mast cell chemotaxis. Mast cell chemotaxis is the movement of a mast cell in response to an external stimulus.

label.value: positive regulation of mast cell chemotaxis

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of mast cell chemotaxis. Mast cell chemotaxis is the movement of a mast cell in response to an external stimulus.

label.value: negative regulation of mast cell chemotaxis

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of mast cell chemotaxis. Mast cell chemotaxis is the movement of a mast cell in response to an external stimulus.

label.value: foraging behavior

value.value: Behavior by which an organism locates food.

label.value: adult foraging behavior

value.value: Behavior by which an adult locates food.

label.value: foraging behavior by probing substrate

value.value: Foraging behavior in which an anatomical part of the organism is inserted into the substrate to locate food.

label.value: regulation of response to cytokine stimulus

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of a response to cytokine stimulus.

label.value: positive regulation of response to cytokine stimulus

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of a response to cytokine stimulus.

label.value: negative regulation of response to cytokine stimulus

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of a response to cytokine stimulus.

label.value: regulation of branching involved in mammary gland duct morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of branching involved in mammary gland duct morphogenesis.

label.value: mammary duct terminal end bud growth

value.value: The morphogenetic growth of the large, club-shaped terminal end of a mammary gland duct during prepubertal growth and during puberty.

label.value: cell-cell signaling involved in mammary gland development

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from one cell to another and contributes to the progression of the mammary gland, from its initial state to the mature structure.

label.value: regulation of androgen receptor signaling pathway

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the androgen receptor signaling pathway.

label.value: negative regulation of androgen receptor signaling pathway

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the androgen receptor signaling pathway.

label.value: epithelial cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of epithelial cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: regulation of epithelial cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of epithelial cell proliferation that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: positive regulation of epithelial cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of epithelial cell proliferation that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: negative regulation of epithelial cell proliferation involved in prostate gland development

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of epithelial cell proliferation that contributes to the progression of the prostate gland over time.

label.value: phyllotactic patterning

value.value: The radial pattern formation process that results in the formation of plant organs (leaves or leaf-like structures) or flower primordia around a central axis.

label.value: leaf phyllotactic patterning

value.value: The radial pattern formation process that results in the formation of leaf primordia around the center of a shoot apical meristem.

label.value: flower phyllotactic patterning

value.value: The radial pattern formation process that results in the formation of floral organ primordia around a central axis in a flower primordium.

label.value: simple leaf morphogenesis

value.value: The leaf morphogenesis process which results in the shaping of a simple leaf. A simple leaf is a leaf in which the lamina is undivided.
